gicians (encounter 3)</span><hr size=1> *ooc this is Tenzing again, and I know I haven’t written in awhile but reading these boards has inspired me to work on my ancient Magician tales, hope you all enjoy*<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Gekn the air elemental held up his scimitar and taunted any of the magicians to step forward and challenge him. &quot;I will give you all a choice of who wants to die first, and honorably&quot; The magicians of the so called strike team stood in paralyzed fear of this elemental, a beast of fifteen feet tall, and eight feet wide. Who would even think of trying to take on something like this, but it was their job, and the evil creature must be sent back to where it came from.<br>
<br>
A wise and powerful Jeneane stepped forward. Jeneane was over five hundred years old and one not to be taken lightly. Her power was only outmatched by her intelligence, one that had seen the world, and knew no fear. Scars of burnt flesh could be seen upon her face, one finger missing from his battle with a dragon many years ago, this was a Mage who had seen it all. Brilliant white hair covered her head, and down to her shoulders. Sharply she looked up upon the elemental before, him, seeing no eyes. Jeneane knew the elemental was looking at her though, feeling its essence bearing deep into her, all around, carefully studying her. After a moment of silence Jeneane spoke. &quot;A grave mistake has been made here, and for that innocent have died from your power, but no more Elemental.&quot; I have seen your kind before, and defeated them. I'm not like any of these mages you see before you; I am Jeneane! With that the mage summoned up a staff in her left hand, and got into a fighting stance, ready for the elemental to make his move. Jeneane was always questioned for not using a staff made by the magician craftsman like all the other mages did, until one day she showed how only a staff summoned by her own power would satisfy her. With her staff she went off to Nektulos to demonstrate it. Finding one of the biggest trees there by the monolith, she took up her conjured staff, and with one swift stroke reduced the tree to a stump. No one after that ever questioned Jeneane again. Her newly summoned staff glowed green in her hand, ever ready to be put into action with Jeneane’s hand clasped tightly around it.<br>
<br>
“We shall see”, Gekn said in his piercing voice, one that made the others wince while Jeneane stood her ground, strong and impermeable. One of Gekn’s hand begin to glow with a blue hue, small little blue round particles began to gather around it. Jeneane could feel an immense power coming from the one concentrated area. With Gekn’s open hand he collected these particles, all massing into the center of his hand, shades of blue visible to all. A great roar let up from Gekn suddenly, raising his left arm with scimitar in hand, he sent it crashing down upon Jeneane, who raised her staff with her left to defend. A great crash of two superior weapons was heard, and with another roar Gekn stretched out his other arm, preparing to fire out his glowing particles of blue energy. “Feel the power of my stun spell” Gekn roared out at Jeneane, but she was to quick for Gekn and ducked, looking up at the huge amount of pure raw power surging over top her head and behind her. With a sudden scream heard from behind, Jeneane managed to turn her head slightly enough to see Renetal being consumed by the energy, it was too powerful of a spell for anyone to survive, a stronger more concentrated version. Watching Renetal all the mages saw the horror of Gekn’s spell. His skin began to form thousands of red blotches, as blood veins busted within him, his eyes filled with red, within seconds, Renetal was a dead mass on the floor of what was once considered a Dark Elf..... <br>
